INSERT INTO activities VALUES ( '4', '[Source: E-mail sent to: info@vote.ph by Michael P. Garay (manggagawa@edsamail.com.ph)]<BR>
<P>
*******************************************<BR>
NEWS RELEASE<BR>
April 24, 2001<BR>
<BR><BR>
<P>
Local leader of PM killed
<P>
At around 7:00 last night, two gunmen shot and killed Manuel Ibe, president of the 1,300-strong labor union of Liwayway Manufacturing and founding member of labor party-list group Partido ng Manggagawa (PM) chapter in Cavite. He was slain in front of the factory gates in Imus as he was going home from work.
<P>
Ibe is a leader of PM in Cavite and was a prominent figure in the group\'s successful province-wide motorcade and chapter founding assembly last Sunday. He is the second leader of the PM to be slain in almost three months, following the assassination of militant labor leader Ka Popoy Lagman last February 6. 
<P>
The group\'s Cavite chapter announced that it will launch mass actions to demand the immediate capture of the suspects and the swift resolution of the murder case.
<P>
According to PM national chairman Renato Magtubo, \"The perpetrators of this grisly act are undoubtedly enemies of the working class. Dark and sinister forces want to derail the PM as they are threatened by labor\'s active participation in mainstream politics.
<P>
\"While the slaying of Ka Popoy was meant to intimidate the PM, which was then in the heat of preparation for its National Founding Congress, the murder of Manuel Ibe intends to terrorize the PM Cavite chapter after its successful founding assembly.\"
<P>
Magtubo added, \"However, we will not be cowed. The party will persevere on its aims and objectives.\"
<P>
He said, \"With barely a few days before Labor Day, militant labor leaders who sincerely strive for the interest of the working class in the parliamentary arena face the iron hand of repression and harassment. If government continuously fails to address this, labor will be forced to struggle through non-parliamentary means.\"
<P>
The group decried the \"evolving pattern of repression against the PM\". Early this month, Reynaldo Lopez, PM organizer for Cavite was arrested. He was released after 3 days of incarceration. ###
<P>

PARTIDO NG MANGGAGAWA ONLINE: http://www.manggagawa.cjb.net
<BR><BR><BR>', '2001-05-01', '605', '28', '0', '0', 'N', 'Email sent to info@vote.ph (4/24)', 'Murder of PM local leader', '20010424163523');
