INSERT INTO activities VALUES ( '8', '<P>
Joint Press Statement <BR>
May 30, 2001<BR>
Sanlakas, Bukluran ng Manggagawang Pilipino, Partido ng Manggagawa<BR>
<BR>
PEOPLE POWER VS. POWER BILL<BR>
<P>
We express our collective resolve to block the passage of the omnibus power bill in the special session of Congress called by President GMA. Against the cute infomercials of GMA and the threats of massive blackouts by Camacho, we are preparing a people power versus the power bill. Daily mobilizations will hound the deliberations of the power bill to warn the honorable members of Congress against betraying the people.
<P>
This pet bill of FVR, Erap and Ate Glo is against the interests of the Filipino people and in favor of big business. The latest proposed amendments to the power bill are merely token concessions that do not alter its anti-people essence which is the privatization of Napocor and its transfer into the hands of the Lopezes and Aboitizes.
<P>
Even the proposed lowering of the power purchase adjustment or PPA from P1.00/kwH to P0.70/kwH is 70 centavos more than what is just and necessary. The consumers should not bear the heavy burden of the PPA. The distribution companies like Meralco should face the consequences of their bad business decisions and not pass it on to consumers. The onerous Napocor contracts with the IPP\'s too must be renegotiated for there is no sense paying for power that is not used or even generated.
<P>
The alleged reduction of electricity rates with the passage of the power bill is just creative marketing. We heard of that before when the privatization of MWSS was being pushed. Electricity will not be cheaper but dearer when power generation, transmission and distribution become private monopolies owned by big business.
<P>
The only reason that the administration is hell bent on passing the new power bill is because it is a conditionality for the release of a multimillion dollar loan from the ADB. The power bill is the prime example of how economic policy is not determined by our national interest--meaning the people\'s welfare--but dictated by foreign institutions which are neither accountable nor mandated by the Filipino people. ###
<BR>
<BR>', '2001-06-05', '605', '0', '0', '0', 'Y', 'E-mail to info@vote.ph (5/31)', 'On the Power Bill', '20010531202347');

