INSERT INTO candrepresentatives VALUES ( '65', 'Cruz', 'Percival Fojas', NULL, '267', '153', 'candrepresentatives - percival cruz.jpg', '1947-06-20', '', '', '', '', '[Source: <A HREF=\"http://www.percycruz.net/myfamily.htm\">http://www.percycruz.net/myfamily.htm</A>]
<P>
I was born to a family in Tondo, Manila. My father was Alberto Segismundo Cruz, a government employee, poet, novelist and storywriter. He was declared by the government the poet-laureate in 1947, maybe this is the equivalent of a National Artist if given today.
</P>
<P>
My mother was Patrocinio Lopez Fojas, a professional housewife and part-time homebound businesswoman. It amazes me up to this day how my father and mother with meager resources were able to raise and educate 10 children. Talk about family planning.
</P>
<P>
The photos, from top to bottom, left to right:
</P>
<P>
My wife Lilian Quiray Matic-Cruz, a Stellan and my former classmate in U.P. She holds a MBA degree in business and was a government scholar in The Netherlands. The boy is our youngest son, Omar Kenji or O.K. Cruz. Someday, I want him to be a professional politician.
</P>
<P>
My eldest daugher Justine Amanda, a born-comic and free spirit, she can survive in any place and any situation.
</P>
<P>
My wife, Lili, again. Currently she is the General Secretary of the Real Estate Brokers Association of the Philippines or REBAP.
</P>
<P>
My father-in-law, well-respected lawyer Tomas P. Matic, Jr. He topped the bar exam during his time and was Government Corporate Counsel during the time of Pres. Diosdado Macapagal. With him, our middle child, Jar-el Almira \"Miki\" - a budding violinist and artist.
</P>
<P>
A photo of my wife and myself that I like very much. This was taken on the shore of Pagudpud Beach near Laoag Ilocos Sur where I brought Taiwanese investors in 1995-96.
</P>
<P>
I bring to public life or public service a family record that is studded with honest efforts, achievements despite limited financial resources, integrity, decency, respect and love between and among its members.
</P>
<P>
We have a deeply religious and patriotic family both on my side and the side of my wife. My family supports 110% my campaign to be the Congressman of the First District of Quezon City and wants to see me champion laws and programs that will strenghthen the family and preserve great Filipino family values, such as, respect for the elders, unity, Christian kindness, respect for nature, honesty, hardwork, and frugality.
</P>', '', 'Manila', 'percy_cruz@netlane.com', '', '', '2', '20010521153613', '[Source <A HREF=\"http://www.percycruz.net/plansandprograms.htm\">http://www.percycruz.net/plansandprograms.htm</A>]<BR><BR>

<B>LOCAL</B>
<P>
<B>Business and Jobs</B>. Create an active and morally healthy business sector in the First District of Q.C. so that jobs can be created for the many who are unemployed; provide opportunities to those who have business inclinations so that they can put up their own business. This means creating incentives to businessmen and technical assistance to small and medium-scale business starters.
</P>
<P>
<B>Quality of Life</B>. Improve the quality of life by getting government funding for infrasructure projects that will improve the traffic situation, provide more schools, clinics, and community centers in the First District of Q.C.
</P>
<P>
Help solve the homelessness problem in the District and the whole country by passing creative home financing laws for the low-income people
</P>
<P>
Close coordination with the PNP to insure peace and order and the collection of garbage
</P>
<P>
<B>Education</B>. The establishment of a free technical college within the First District that will teach the youth how to acquire skills and how to be financially independent
</P>
<P>
<B>CDF</B>. The Comunity Development Fund (CDF) will be used in all transparency and will finance the deserving projects of the Barangays and civic groups, including the granting of scholarships to poor students
</P>
<P>
<B>Unity</B>. The organization of regular Town Hall Meetings where all the sectors of the District will come to discuss and solve the District’s problems 
</P>
<P>
<B>Morality</B>. Launch a moral crusade so that the district and entire cities may be reached for Christ through community prayer and evangelism
</P>
<B>NATIONAL</B>
<P>
An <B>Omnibus Anti-Discrimination Law</B> that will protect and give equal opportunities to today\'s second-class citizens:  the poor, the senior citizens, the minority cultures and religions, the gays and homosexuals and the handicapped.  These citizens constitute a national resource that is wasted because our society does not give opportunities to them. 
</P>
<P>
Quick-start the <B>removal of trade barriers</B> - zero or minimal customs duties, so that every citizen can become a businessman, a manufacturer or a trader. 
</P>
<P>
Join the momentum in <B>making Mindanao the food basket of the Philippines</B> and, if possible, of the world. Help bring peace and evangelization in Mindanao.
</P>', '', 'Percy', '', '657', '0', 'N', '');
