INSERT INTO candrepresentatives VALUES ( '72', 'Villanueva', 'Joel Emmanuel', NULL, '546', '0', 'candrepresentatives - joel emmanuel villanueva.jpg', '0000-00-00', '', '', '', '', '', '[Source <A HREF=\"http://www.cibac.org/about.html\">http://www.cibac.org/about.html</A>]
<P>
In the Philippines, there seems to be a tendency for many to doubt the capabilities of the youth. Believing that somehow, potential to accomplish great deeds is directly proportional to age. If that were true, then the first representative of CIBAC could not possibly exist. Joel Villanueva, all of 25 years old, has worked hard to make his mark in society. As the current managing director of ZOE TV Channel 11, Joel has been the moving force behind ZOE\'s thrust to provide quality programming for millions of viewers. In addition, he is the chairman of the Kristianong Kabataan Para Bayan (KKB) and the Ministry of HELPS, a socio-civic group providing assistance to calamity victims. He was also a recepient of the Gloria Macapagal Arroyo leadership Award in 1996 as well as a 2-time RP Youth member, representing the country in international basketball competitions. 
<P>
But perhaps his most laudable trait is that he does not find any reason to rest on his laurels. Instead, he has turned his attention towards the people\'s fight against a formidable foe - corruption. Joel is offering his youth and desire to rid the government of this scourge which has been thought by many skeptics as an unsolvable problem. A quixotic spirit in this young man? Perhaps. But that\'s what brought him this far, and would serve him well as the first representative of CIBAC.', '', '', '', '', '0', '20010418102805', '', '', '', '', '0', '0', 'N', '');
INSERT INTO candrepresentatives VALUES ( '73', 'Bernardo', 'Kim', NULL, '546', '0', 'candrepresentatives - kim bernardo.jpg', '0000-00-00', '', '', '', '', '', '[Source <A HREF=\"http://www.cibac.org/about.html\">http://www.cibac.org/about.html</A>]
<P>
Lately, there has been a call to scrutinize media and showbiz candidates running for public office. Many seem to feel that these candidates simply make use of their popularity and their connections with media to catapult them into office without any real capacity to hold it. A skeptic would be quick about dismissing Kim as a CIBAC representative. Pretty, charming and outspoken, she could easily fit stereotypes made to show why media personalities should not be allowed to hold office. At least, on the surface, that is. It takes a closer look to reveal that Kim is actually be one of those who would actually insure a responsive, dynamic system of government that the people deserve. 
<P>
Kim Bernardo Lokin is a dedicated broadcast journalist who has steadfastly upheld her commitment to educate and inform the public on issues of national importance. For nearly a decade, Kim Bernardo-Lokin covered major news events enabling her to be familiar with key branches of government ---- Malacanang, Senate, Department of Justice and the NBI. As senior Senate reporter, Kim anchored ABS-CBN News Channel\'s Senate At Work from 1994-1995, giving the viewers a daily update of activities at the Upper House. 
<P>
In 1996, Kim was tapped to anchor the daily business program \"Stock Market Live\" also at the ABS CBN News Channel (ANC) a post she held for three years before getting her break as a primetime current affairs anchor of \"Moneywise\" a business magazine program which she hosted with Gilbert Remulla.', '', '', '', '', '0', '20010418103020', '', '', '', '', '0', '0', 'N', '');
INSERT INTO candrepresentatives VALUES ( '74', 'Martinez', 'Atty. Jesus', NULL, '546', '0', 'candrepresentatives - atty jesus martinez.jpg', '0000-00-00', '', '', '', '', '', '[Source <A HREF=\"http://www.cibac.org/about.html\">http://www.cibac.org/about.html</A>]
<P>
Some say it is impossible in Philippine politics to find a successful marriage of good, moral values and political acumen in today\'s candidates. If that is true, then CIBAC truly is fortunate. Its third candidate, Atty. Jess Martinez, not only has both, but also manages to get his ideals across in a very down-to-earth and affable manner. He is remarkable in the sense that he has no puffed-up sense of self-importance about him, as many political hopefuls often try to project. His firm handshake and ever-present smile give an impression that he is just another citizen who is willing to serve if given a chance. It is an impression that is nothing but correct. 
<P>
Born in Manila to parents Jesus and Winifred Martinez, Jess has never shown anything but his competence and willingness to serve throughout his life. A lawyer by profession, he has handled many litigation cases for various local and foreign corporations for 15 years. In the political arena, he has been a former board member and later vice-mayor of Negros Oriental, where he served his constituents with the zeal expected of a servant of the public. 
<P>
Jess is also a lay minister of the Community Church of Las Pinas and Fil-American Church in Long Beach, U.S.A. He is married to Cheryl Lynn Jubela-Martinez and they have three children, Michelle Lynn, Monica, and Jesus Gianpaolo III.', '', '', '', '', '0', '20010418103230', '', '', 'Jess', '', '0', '0', 'N', '');
