Who is Boy Seseng de los Angeles?
<P>
Celso Gancayco de los Angeles<BR>
“Boy Seseng”<BR>
Date of birth: August 6, 1952<BR>
Address: 206 J.P. Rizal St., Sta. Elena, Marikina City<BR>
Married to: Concepcion Arguelles Panlilio<BR>
Children: Martin Nicolo P. de los Angeles<BR>
Paolo Vicente P. de los Angeles  <BR>
<P>
Celso Gancayco de los Angeles, Jr. also known as “Boy Seseng” is the great grandson of the founder of the Shoe Industry, Laureano “Kapitan Moy” Guevara. He is a native Marikeno. His father, the late Dr. Celso Guevara de los Angeles or “Dr. Seseng” was a very much-loved physician in Marikina. He was one of the internationally well respected authorities in the field of pulmonary medicine. In Marikina, he was often referred to as “Doktor ng Bayan”. The mother of Boy Seseng is Purita Gancayco de los Angeles. She is still very active in the Catholic Women’s League, where she was the former National Director. She is also a trustee of the Sandigan Foundation. Boy Seseng’s grandfather on his father’s side, the late Don Servando Manahan de los Angeles ran for Congress in the 2nd district of the Province of Rizal.
<P>
Mr. Celso G. de los Angeles, Jr., more popular known as “Boy Seseng” hailed from Marikina, the shoe capital of the Philippines. His Father, a dedicated physician was fondly called by his patients and friends as Dr. Seseng and his mother, Purita Gancayco de los Angeles who isstill living at their family house where he grew up in Brgy. Sta. Elena is known in the neighborhood as Dona Purita. The desire of his loving parents to provide him a better life in the future sent him to an exclusive school, Ateneo de Manila University where he completed his education from grade school to college. He pursued his studies and took up his Masters in Business Administration at the Asian Institute of Management, the country’s premier school in Management.
<P>
Boy Seseng has also his ups and downs but he believes that there is an opportunity in every crisis. He realized how much more persons can do it if they go beyond what appears to be their limits. “If you dreamed the best for yourself, you usually get,” as he often emphasized to his employees. His experiences in the USA for almost 14 years where he was even forced to apply as a security guard and as a gasoline attendant served as an inspiration and encouragement for his work force. And while working, he took time to study and finish a course in Free Legal Administration Management at Georgetown University in Washinton D.C.
<P>
In 1996, when Mr. Celso G. de los Angeles, Jr. returned to the Philippines, he was welcomed by an offer to venture in the pre-need business and joined a fast growing educational plan company, Scholarship Plan Philippines Inc., as Chairman and CEO. Although he did not know the industry very well, he considered it as a challenge, and his financial expertise had gained him a firm base in this new endeavor. However, he realized that a one-product company does not only limit its market share but the profit margin as well and on December 5, 1998 Celso G. de los Angeles, Jr. acquired Legacy Plans Inc., as majority owner and launched the most competitive pension plan in the market.
<P>
As a banker and a businessman, Mr. Celso G. de los Angeles, Jr., inspired by his great grandfather, Don Laureano “Kapitan Moy” Guevarra who set up the first shoe industry, has a special concern for the shoe industry and putting up a Marikina Shoe bank partly owned by shoe manufacturers and partly owned by the government is his most cherished dream. He stressed that shoemakers in Marikina if given the right support can craft shoes and accessories that could compete in the fashion centers of Paris, London, New Yorkm and Tokyo and even penetarate the global market.
<P>
His outstanding performance attained through the years will serve as benchmarks for greater achievements ahead. His innovative management, pioneering efforts and the commitment to the business will surely lead to futher improve performance, set higher standards and enhance human resources capability particularly in the fields of marketing to face greater challenges and set the tone for the next millennium.', 'Marikina City', 'bosesnatin@hotmail.com', '', '6461575', '2', '20010508105210', '', '', 'Boy Seseng', '', '0', '0', 'N', '');
