INSERT INTO candsenators VALUES ( '25', 'Pagdanganan', 'Roberto', 'M', '233', 'candsenator - roberto pagdanganan.jpg', '1946-07-19', '', '', '[Source: <A HREF=\"http://www.obet.ph/platform.htm\">http://www.obet.ph/platform.htm</A>]<BR><BR>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><B>A Legislative 
Agenda</B></FONT></P>
<P><B><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">THE POLITICS OF 
PERFORMANCE</FONT></B><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><BR><BR>By 
F/Gov. Obet Pagdanganan</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">Our Legislative Agenda envisions to 
free every Filipino from the chain of poverty, from the threats of crime and 
repression; and, instead, to nurture in everyone the will, the drive and the 
energy to dream and achieve a just, humane and progressive society.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">EDSA II manifested the demand of 
the people for transparency in all aspect of governance. All officials must be 
accountable to the public; those who seek public office must justify their 
quest.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">Politics of performance and not 
just popularity is the urgent need of our times, given that the Constitution 
mandates \"...public trust and all government officials and employees must serve 
with utmost degree of responsibility, integrity, loyalty and 
efficiency.\"</FONT></P>
<P></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">I. ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT.<BR><BR>* 
Pursue a free-market economy with \"less government in business but more business 
in government\"<BR><BR>* Ensure food security with support systems to the 
agricultural sectors like post-harvest facilities, irrigation, cooperative 
development, inter-cooperative trading, easier access to resources and 
opportunities.<BR><BR>* Streamline all national government agencies involved in 
livelihood programs into a one-stop agency which supports SMEs (small and medium 
enterprises) with access to capital, market and technology.<BR><BR>*Restructure 
policies and procedures to attract foreign investments.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Strengthen the synergy between 
government, non-governmental organizations (NGOs) and the private 
sector.<BR><BR>* Bring down the interest rates to spur business without fueling 
inflation.<BR><BR>* Discourage wasteful consumption to inspire savings at all 
levels of society and institutions.<BR></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">II.LOCAL AUTONOMY.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Implement genuine local autonomy 
to transform Local Government Units (LGUs) into pro-active partners of the 
national government to accelerate country-side development.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Institute amendments to the Local 
Government Code like these priorities:</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Increase the Internal Revenue 
Allotment (IRA) of LGUs from 40% to 50% by year 2002.The increment of the 
increase over the previous year shall be allocated based on the LGU performance 
and the scarcity of resources vis-a-vis the needs for development of poorer 
LGUs.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Expand LGU authority to tax, i.e 
registration fees on-tonne vessels and below, excise tax on NIRC articles, 
except petroleum products.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Simplify local tax 
structures.<BR><BR>* Stop unfunded mandates; instead, allocate funds to cover 
the cost of devolved services.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Greater participation of the 
civil society in LGU affairs to ensure accountability and 
transparency.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Transfer to the LGU the 
authority, supervision, and control of the police forces.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">III. ELECTRORAL REFORMS</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Promote a system of politics 
based on party ideology, principles and programs.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Institutionalize voter education 
to minimize pernicious electoral frauds like the infamous 
\"Dagdag-Bawas\"</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Strengthen party system by 
installing election inspectors for the two leading parties of the immediately 
preceeding election.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Establish public funding of the 
two leading political parties to encourage deserving leaders who may not have 
the necessary finances. Parties will, thus be obliged to establish a system of 
selecting their candidates based on credentials and willingness to serve. Those 
elected will owe their loyalty to the people and not to selfish vested 
interests.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">IV. QUALITY EDUCATION FOR 
ALL.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Make quality education accessible 
to all.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Provide incentives to teachers 
seeking higher education in their chosen field of expertise.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Encourage emphasis on mathematics 
and sciences where the Filipino youth lag behind.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Encourage government partnership 
with private education sector.<BR><BR>* Include pre-schooling in the basic 
educational curriculum<BR><BR>* Expand scholarship and study-now-pay-later 
programs for poor but deserving students.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><BR>V. WAR AGAINTS GRAFT AND 
CORRUPTION.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Review systems and procedures to 
eliminate redundant steps which become avenues for graft and 
corruption.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Institute value formation program 
with a massive information drive againts graft and corruption.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">* Encourage civil participation by 
providing just rewards and secured protection.</FONT></P>
<P></P>
