(1959).</FONT></P>', 'Calumpit, Bulacan', '', '', '', '2', '20010623104303', '', '', 'Obet', '', '7111681', '1', '5367475', 'N', '405556', '188005', '1213846', '962647', '411061', '656421', '699936', '314061', '206829', '182061', '273532', '125571', '134669', '149192', '1018788', '169325', '181', '');
INSERT INTO candsenators VALUES ( '26', 'Pangilinan', 'Francis', 'N', '230', 'candsenator - francis pangilinan.jpg', '1963-08-24', '', '', '<P align=center><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>KILOS KO 
MANIFESTO </B></FONT></P>
<P align=center><B><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>New Politics 
For &amp; By the New Generation </FONT></B></P>
<P align=center><B><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Preamble 
</FONT></B></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Aware that the People Power 
Revolution Part II has again catalyzed the citizens of the land to unite against 
a corrupt and immoral regime and to renew their zeal for personal conviction, 
good governance, \"new\" politics and genuine democracy; </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Recognizing that the change 
of national leadership is not the ultimate solution to progress, democracy, 
peace and social justice but is merely a means towards the realization of these 
national goals; </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Realizing that the Filipino 
people continue to clamor for a graft-free and efficient government, 
transparency and accountability in public service, social responsibility on the 
part of business and the private sector, renewed decency and morality permeating 
from families to larger social units, livelihood opportunities in their own 
land, sustainable and equitable development, relevant and scientific educational 
systems, and competitiveness in the global arena; </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Noting that majority of the 
population are young, but the youth remains disenfranchised in political and 
decision-making processes that directly affect them; </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Convinced that only through 
the active participation of the citizens, particularly the youth, in democratic 
processes and in public affairs would the country overcome the magnitude of its 
political, economic and social problems and move towards meaningful solutions 
and reforms; </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>NOW, THEREFORE, KILOS KO 
proclaims this Manifesto as standards for the principles and polic</FONT><FONT 
face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>ies in campaigning for Atty. Francis 
\"Kiko\" N. Pangilinan for Senator.</FONT></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P align=center><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>Candidate\'s 
Vision</B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I am working for the 
Philippines, my country, the only one I have. This is my move of faith and 
courage.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I am taking charge. I am a 
youth, the future of this nation is mine. I am a responsible citizen, taking 
stand for what is right, refusing to compromise with evil, working to recreate a 
country I can look forward to the future with optimism and hope, where I can 
become the very best I can be, all I was created to be, where my personal 
ambitions and dreams can become a reality, where I will be proud to raise my own 
family someday.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I will work to and persevere 
to make this vision become reality. I will not allow inconvenience, 
discouragement and doubt to deter me. I will not allow the forces of evil to 
steal, kill and destroy the only country I have. </FONT></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P align=center><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>Candidates 
Mission </B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I will work to elect 
God-fearing public servants who will uphold the values of honor, decency, heart 
and justice for those in need. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>My immediate task: I will 
start by putting Kiko Pangilinan and like-minded persons in the 
Senate.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I commit to learn everything 
that is relevant about the electoral process, the candidates and the dynamics of 
political process.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I will be proactive and 
vigilant in encouraging and demanding transparency, accountability, and 
competence in public servants.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I will work to expose and 
convict the corrupt and incompetent in government.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I volunteer my time, my 
talents, and my resources toward the achievement of this mission.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>I will share what I know 
with others and encourage them to make this move, too.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Recreating my country begins 
with me. </FONT></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P align=center><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>Legislative 
Agenda </B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>The face of Philippine 
politics has begun to morph, transformed by the miracle that was EDSA II. We 
witnessed the youth taking a stand for its future, the combined power of media 
and new technology in disseminating information, in increasing political 
awareness and consciousness triggered and unleashed by the power of an 
enlightened citizenry demanding truth, justice, and accountability from public 
officials in the highest places. Should our people grant me the privilege to 
serve in the Senate, the causes I will champion would focus on: </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>1. New politics and 
paradigm shifts in leadership and governance </B></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Strengthening 
accountability, and transparency</FONT> 
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>encouraging 
vision-orientedness, proactive policies and value-driven performance in public 
service </FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>2. Corrupt-free and swift 
justice </B></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>creating a more transparent 
judicial system, specifically the courts by providing them with the technology 
and training that will enable the public tracking of cases in progress 
</FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>3. Education for national 
progress and global competitiveness </B></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>channeling resources toward 
investments in the upgrade of the quality of teaching, upgrading compensation 
and providing them with access to information technology</FONT> </LI></UL>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>4. Creation of wealth and 
income opportunities </B></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>institutionalizing market 
research and database forecasting and forward-thinking that will anticipate 
market needs and provide opportunities for new employment entrants </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>providing incentives and 
simplifying the propagation of small- and medium-scale business investments 
</FONT>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>assessing the social costs 
of the OCW and providing a job-creation drive to ultimately reunite and 
strengthen Filipino families</FONT> </LI></UL>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P align=center><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>Summary 
</B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>Kiko para sa Kabataan, 
Katarungan, Kabuhayan at Kinabukasan </B></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>the citizenry, particularly 
the youth, must take an active role in governance</FONT> 
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>government sector must 
institutionalize accountability, transparency, vision-orientedness, and 
value-driven performance </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>judicial courts must be 
made more efficient by continuous education of personnel and by the use of 
appropriate technology </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>increase resources in 
education and prioritize teacher training and educational materials development 
· proactive training and allocation of human resources</FONT> 
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>prioritize incentives and 
support for small- and medium-scale industries</FONT> 
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>provide opportunities for 
local employment to reduce social costs of OCW\'s </FONT></LI></UL>
<P>&nbsp;</P>', '', '', '', 'Manila', '', '', '', '2', '20010623104303', '', '', 'Kiko', '', '10877989', '1', '8233974', 'Y', '776895', '306577', '1448029', '1599024', '563894', '1066264', '1031794', '486491', '306165', '331500', '533454', '184896', '174194', '164429', '1610367', '293830', '186', '');
INSERT INTO candsenators VALUES ( '27', 'Puno', 'Ricardo Jr.', 'V', '243', 'candsenator - ricardo puno.jpg', '1946-01-20', '', '', '<P align=center><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>DONG PUNO\'S 
CAMPAIGN PLATFORM</B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>In running for senator under 
the Laban ng Demokratikong Pilipino (Laban) ticket, Dong Puno has an eight-point 
program designed to help Government uplift the living standards of our people. 
What he is pledged to do, particularly for those at the grassroots level, can be 
summed up in two words--- <B>DONG PUNO</B> </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>This acronym stands for the 
following:</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B><FONT size=4>D</FONT></B> 
- dunong </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Strengthening basic 
education is the ultimate social equalizer: it will give the rich and the poor 
equal opportunities to quality learning. Hence, Dong Puno is in favor of a 
closer cooperation between the Executive Branch and Congress in shifting the 
bulk of the education budget from tertiary to basic education. To correct the 
current education job mismatch, he is for selecting - and further developing - 
Centers of Excellence from among the existing educational institutions in each 
region and province. Schools should also closely coordinate with the various 
industries to determine the real demand of employers in each sector. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=4><B>O</B></FONT><FONT 
face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2> - oportunidad</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Any program to expand 
opportunities of jobs or livelihood endeavors should consider the masses in the 
countryside. Therefore, Dong Puno will support moves to fully implement the 
Agricultural and Fisheries Modernization Act, which is anchored on a 
labor-intensive rural infrastructure buildup. He will also back measures to 
improve the Philippine capability to supply qualified workers in the area of 
information technology or IT. There is also the problem of providing retraining 
for overseas workers, many of whom want to return home but are prevented from 
doing so by the lack of opportunities back home. To improve opportunities for 
acquiring low-cost homes, he also supports a government policy designed to 
sustain a demand-driven approach to housing. The supply driven policy in the 
pre-Estrada era resulted in costly mistakes that we should not repeat. He is for 
development of resettlement for squatters that include not only adequate basic 
services but also livelihood opportunities. N - No to drugs The drug problem is 
now very serious. Dong Puno supports taking a firm stand against drug 
trafficking and dealing a hard blow against those involved in the supply side of 
this scourge. There is also a need to focus on prevention and improving the 
rehabilitation system for victims of drug abuse. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=4><B>G</B></FONT><FONT 
face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2> - good government &amp; 
justice</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Dong Puno believes that 
corruption and congestion of court cases are the two main problems of judicial 
administration. Competent lawyers should be attracted to the bench by offering 
them competitive salary scale and fringe benefits. The court should be made the 
bulwarks of equity and justice. The perception of some that the courts are a 
market place where life and liberties are traded to the highest bidder must be 
reversed. He also wants to pursue the rehabilitation of the penal system so that 
offenders would come out of prison moulded into useful citizens 
again.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><FONT size=4><B>P</B></FONT> 
- puno at pagkain </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>For Dong Puno, issues 
concerning the environment should take into account the welfare of the sectors 
who depend on the environment for survival. These include the poor who rely on 
our farmlands and our forests for their means of livelihood. Thus, Dong Puno 
will support programs and policies that promote sustainable development and at 
the same time provide jobs and alternative livelihood opportunities for sectors 
that may be displaced or adversely affected as a result of these initiatives. 
Sustainable development should meet the requirements of the present generation 
of Filipinos without endangering the capacity of future generations to meet 
their own needs. Dong Puno also believes that now is the time for Government to 
come up with a realistic program to finally deal with our forest denudation. He 
will spearhead a drive in the Senate so that Congress can pass legislation that 
will resolve the problem of deforestation and allow reasonable commercial 
activities to ensure the welfare of dependents in wood-based industries, upland 
dwellers and other affected sectors. He believes that due regard should also be 
given to the legitimate concerns of responsible loggers who have a clear and 
sustained reforestation program in place. He will likewise push for the full 
implementation of the Clean Air Act, but with the welfare of the Filipino masa 
in mind. Also, Dong Puno will support a massive infrastructure buildup in the 
country that will help sustain and even improve upon the gains of our food 
security programs. His focus will be on building more farm-to-market roads, 
irrigation projects and post-harvest facilities.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B><FONT size=4>U</FONT></B> 
- unity and peace </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Dong Puno considers peace 
and order as a vital factor in maintaining investor confidence and sustaining 
economic growth. Thus, he will support programs addressing poverty, particularly 
in areas where communist and Muslim insurgencies are rampant. For him, the 
government should mount more aggressive efforts to continue the peace 
process.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B><FONT size=4>N</FONT></B> 
- nasyonalismo</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Dong Puno believes in the 
ability and capability of the Filipino people to handle whatever difficulties 
confront them. He is pushing Laban\'s politics of hope or optimism. As you can 
see, his campaign is anchored on \"Puno ng Pag-asa para sa Masa.\" This brand of 
Filipino nationalism can be expected to be further developed, with the 
successful implementation of the above-mentioned initiatives. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=4>O </FONT><FONT 
face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>- open communication</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>The former press secretary 
and presidential spokesman believes that a free press is a vital instrument in 
the development of an informed and responsible citizenry. Legitimate journalists 
are true fiscalizers who help prevent or expose government abuses. Dong Puno is 
for an unfettered media that protect our citizens, while remaining committed to 
high professional ethical standards and the basic tenets of professional 
journalism. He is also committed to support measures that will ensure the 
regular employment of journalists, especially the provincial correspondents, as 
well as provide them with more benefits, such as insurance and hazard pay. 
</FONT></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>', '', '', '', 'Manila', '', '', '', '2', '20010623104303', '', '', 'Dong', '', '8656568', '2', '6547447', 'N', '478071', '261547', '1129269', '1554409', '291621', '522396', '398746', '341471', '264377', '377319', '737039', '339154', '106964', '64243', '1581540', '208119', '283', '');
INSERT INTO candsenators VALUES ( '28', 'Rasul', 'Santanina', 'T', '465', 'candsenator - santanina rasul.jpg', '1930-09-14', '', '', '<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>There can be no lasting 
peace and true development for the entire Philippines if a large part of our 
society languish in poverty. The armed conflict waged by Muslim extremist and 
the NPAs is the violent response by oppressed citizens who have nothing to lose. 
</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>There can be no true peace 
and development in the entire country if the flames of secession continue to be 
stoked in Mindanao. Ours is a world of global and instantaneous communication, 
where time and space is compressed into a living room. Investments, tourism, and 
trade will continue to stay away from Mindanao, Manila, Cebu, for as long as 
scenes like those we saw of the Abu Sayyaf and MILF encounters play in living 
rooms all over the world.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>There can be no permanent 
peace and development if our poor are shackled by ignorance.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>There can be no true peace 
and development if there are sectors of our society who feel that they are not 
treated equally before the law.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>THERE CAN BE NO PEACE AND 
DEVELOPMENT WITHOUT </B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>RECONCILIATION</B> and 
<B>UNDERSTANDING.</B> helped in the peace negotiations with the MNLF and was 
awarded the Golden Heart Presidential Award. Currently working with Konrad 
Adenauer Foundation to implement a training program for women as mediators in 
Muslim Mindanao. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>ALLEVIATION OF 
POVERTY</B>. her NGO has been providing livelihood training programs for the 
rural poor in Sulu, Tawi-Tawi and Basilan, and the Zamboanga Peninsula for 
almost 20 years now. Established a training school in Sulu for modern 
agriculture technology.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>SUSTAINABLE 
DEVELOPMENT.</B> established the Bantay Dagat, Inc. in 1994 to help protect our 
coastal and marine resources. The Bantay Dagat, Inc. has won 3 national awards 
to date. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2><B>UPLIFTMENT OF 
SECTORS.</B> </FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Empower women : ( March 8 
as Women\'s Day); RA 7192 which opened PMA to women and mandated that part of 
foreign grants be set aside for women\'s projects; section in the Local 
Government Code which provides for a sectoral seat for women in local government 
legislative bodies; provide funds for the UP Women\'s Studies Building in Diliman 
and the Women\'s Support Center in Zamboanga City</FONT> </LI></UL>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>RA 6656 to protect civil 
servants from termination without due process; RA 6850 gave Civil Service 
eligibility to government employees who had served for at least 7 years; RA 6683 
provided attractive retirement benefits to early retirees.</FONT> </LI></UL>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Protect the indigenous 
people\'s land</FONT> </LI></UL>
<P><B><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>LITERACY AND 
EDUCATION</FONT></B><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>. Magbassa 
Kita, a 30-year old program provides literacy training nationwide. She provided 
computer training programs for poor high school graduates and scholarships for 
deserving Muslim youth. Magbassa Kita has benefited hundreds of thousands poor 
Filipinos, composed of youth, adult, women, prisoners, farmers, cured lepers. 
Converted the Philippine Normal College to a university. </FONT></P>', '', '', '', 'Siasi, Sulu', '', '', '', '2', '20010623104303', '', '', 'Nina', '', '5085199', '0', '3829440', 'N', '198085', '124524', '594239', '890150', '109666', '171788', '147967', '174482', '244362', '240725', '475127', '293633', '60932', '224073', '1020334', '114996', '116', '');
