<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>A lawyer by profession, 
Mayor Alvin B. Garcia has been serving the Cebuanos for 12 years now. He was 
elected vice-mayor of the city of Cebu in 1989 and re-elected in 1992. During 
his tenure as vice-mayor, he authored the necessary legislation and ordinances 
needed to push forward the city\'s social and economic agenda. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>He was elected mayor of Cebu 
City in 1995 and re-elected in 1998. As mayor, he focused his efforts on the 
delivery of basic services, employment creation, city hall administrative reform 
and tourism promotion for economic development. As a result, Cebu City has 
registered one of the highest growth rates in real estate and business tax 
collection in the country for the past four years. </FONT></P><FONT 
face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=2>Mayor Garcia completed his law 
studies at the Ateneo de Manila University and passed the bar in 1971. He 
finished his Bachelor of Arts in Political Science with Honors, also at the 
Ateneo. He is married to Ninette Neri and they are blessed with three sons: Jess 
Anthony, Jerald Mark and Raymond Alvin.</FONT> 
