INSERT INTO party VALUES ( '605', 'Partido Ng Manggagawa', 'PM', '2001', 'Y', '0', '2', '0', '0', '', '<P>
The Partido ng Manggagawa or PM aims to be the political and electoral party of the working class in the Philippines. If in other countries, especially in Europe, labor parties represent the workers, then PM is its equivalent in the country.
<P>
The Partido ng Manggagawa was established at the Bahay ng Alumni last February 12 on very the day that labor leader Ka Popoy Lagman was laid to rest. At the time of his death, Ka Popoy was devoting his time into setting up and laying the groundwork for the Partido ng Manggagawa.
<P>
Currently registered as a party-list group, PM will actively participate in the coming elections. PM will campaign to put three representatives in Congress. The party-list nominees of PM are three union presidents--Rene Magtubo of Fortune Tobacco, Victor Briz of Gelmart Industries and Gerry Rivera of PALEA. Aside from the three representatives targeted to sit in Congress through the party-list, PM will be fielding candidates in the local elections.
<P>
The Partido ng Mangagawa is the magic formula to unite the fragmented labor movement and organize the millions of unorganized workers. It is also the missing link to advance the struggle of the working for protection against the scourge of globalization.
<P>
Founded on the belief that existing formations such as local unions and labor federations are limited in their capacity to effectively protect the workers’ interests in this age of globalization, PM will bring the struggle within the parliament. The goal of its participation in the elections is to enact pro-labor legislation and ensure the implementation of pro-worker policies. Its minimum platform is the protection of workers’ interests; its maximum platform is the emancipation of the working class.
<P>
Here lies the stark difference of Partido ng Manggagawa from other political parties. While the traditional political parties pretentiously claim to stand for the interests of the poor, PM will clearly carry the workers’ class standpoint. All of these traditional political parties are proven and undeniably pro-capitalist. The platform, leadership and membership of PM, in its heart and soul, are purely for the interests of every workingman.
<P>
PM is organized at the grassroots level, with individual memberships. Therefore, PM will go beyond existing labor formations and federations since PM membership is not union-based. Each member will undergo seminars and orientation regarding PM before being considered full-pledged PM members. This kind of organizational formation is geared towards developing the labor vote in the Philippines.
<P>
Partido ng Manggagawa believes and will work for the creation of a solid labor vote. For years, labor has given their vote to traditional politicians for the mere fact that there is no political party concretely carrying their interests. With the establishment of the Partido ng Manggagawa, workers nationwide will have a party with which they can confidently give their vote and believe that this party will truly fight for their cause.
<P>
The concept of a labor vote is the like the block voting delivered by Iglesia ni Cristo or El Shaddai. Manalo or Velarde do not have to go to Malacanang to get a hearing, instead politicians and officials themselves pay their respects to the two religious leaders. The labor vote during elections and labor power in the streets will compel the government and politicians not to ignore the voice and demands of the working class.
<P>
The creation of a distinct and solid labor vote will be PM’s main weapon in carrying out its platform. The labor vote, with a single command, will be used for the government to give due respect to the working class. The labor vote will give a lesson to anyone who will go against the interests of the working class. This unity of the working class, and not the PM itself, will ultimately be the direct and actual instrument that will bring about the social change and social justice for the working class.', '<P>
Ipaglalaban ng Partido ng Manggagawa sa Kongreso at lansangan ang mga sumusunod:
<P>
<B>Minimum:</B> Proteksyon ng manggagawa sa salot na globalisasyon.
<UL>
<LI>Ipaglalaban ang sapat na sweldo para mabuhay nang disente at marangal ang isang pamilya. Lalabanan ang cheap labor policy ng gubyerno.
<LI>Ipaglalaban ang kaseguruhan sa trabaho. Lalabanan ang contractualization at downsizing.
<LI>Ipaglalaban ang sapat at regular na trabaho para sa mga Pilipino. 
<LI>Ipaglalaban ang Magna Carta for Unionism para sa malaya at mabilis na pagtatayo ng unyon sa lahat ng uri ng trabaho para proteksyonan ang manggagawa. Lalabanan ang union busting.
<LI>Ipaglalaban ang pagtataas ng labor standard gaya ng 3 buwang maternity pay, 50% overtime premium, pagdoble ng separation pay, 14th Month Pay, palakihin ang pensyon sa SSS at GSIS, walang withholding tax sa sumasahod ng 500/araw pababa, pabahay, insurance sa pagkatanggal sa trabaho, at health insurance sa lahat ng manggagawa.
</UL>
<P>
<B>Maksimum:</B> Lalabanan ang bulok na sistemang pinagmumulan ng mga problema ng manggagawa at ng buong sambayanan at tumulong sa pagbubuo ng isang bagong lipunang may pagpapahalaga sa dignidad ng paggawa, masagana, makatarungan, makatao at higit sa lahat, walang sahurang pang-aalipin.', '<B>Year Founded:</B>&nbsp;February 12, 2001 (Founding Congress)', '', 'manggagawa@edsamail.com.ph', '4364549, 9250884', '#47 Masikap St., Bgy. Pinyahan, Quezon City, Philippines', '4364549', '20010423203435', '', '', '2001');
