INSERT INTO party VALUES ( '648', 'Volunteers Against Crime And Corruption Inc.', 'VACC', '0', 'Y', '0', '2', '0', '0', '', '', '[Source: Sent by <A HREF=\"mailto:vacc@pacific.net.ph\">vacc@pacific.net.ph</A> to info@vote.ph]<BR><BR>
<B>WHY VACC WANTS REPRESENTATION IN CONGRESS</B>
<P>
We\'re giving the electoral struggle a chance where we can assert our rights as crime victims and survivors.
<P>
We realize we cannot expect much from the present political set-up to deal firmly with crime and crime victims. The government has not eliminated the conditions that foster crime.  And when a crime is committed, the chief concern of criminal justice agencies has been apprehending and dealing with the criminal, and that the  victim  or witness is frequently forgotten or further victimized by the criminal justice system. 
<P>
We believe that the present justice system in the country provides more rights and attention to perpetrators of crime than to victims.  Crime victims have few participatory rights, too few agencies/organizations providing scarce services and assistance and no laws passed that articulate and protect victims’ rights like in other countries. The number of crime victims is increasing by leaps and bounds.  Certainly, VACC and crime victims’ groups would not want any increase in their membership anymore.  
<P>
How the justice system will handle itself in pursuing justice for the Filipino people as victims of Erap\'s criminal and corrupt governance is a test case. Just the same, there is a need to institutionalize a law basically working for the interests of victims of crime, particularly of common crimes.
<P>
We want Congress to pass a Crime Victims Rights Law that will give victims the same dignity, respect, and rights afforded the other players in the criminal justice system. A Law that recognizes victims\' rights that includes five basic rights: 
<P>
<OL>
<LI>the right to be treated with dignity and respect, 
<LI>the right to be informed; 
<LI>the right to be present; 
<LI>the right to be compensated and 
<LI>the right to be heard throughout the criminal justice process. 
</OL>
<P>
<B>VACC LEGISLATIVE  AGENDA</B>
<P>
VACC believes that crime is a social menace.  But corruption is a social base of criminality.  Crime and corruption are symptoms of social inequalities in Philippine society.  These social inequalities produce the poverty of the many.  And the poverty of the many stems from the greed of the few.    That is why our battle cry is :  fight crime and corruption!   Because they are symptoms of a larger problem,  VACC believes that to attack at the roots of the problem, we must address the social roots.  THAT can be done with crime victims being in solidarity with the basic sectors of society fighting for social justice.
<P>
Since year 2000, over 100,000 Filipinos  were victims of heinous  crimes. These do not include other victims like the victims of war in Mindanao and political violence.  These aren\'t just statistics, they\'re people.   Their lives and the lives of their families have been changed forever. 
<P>
Therefore,  VACC must work for securing basic changes that must be institutionalized in the Philippine justice system.   It must work along with other sectors in promoting wholistic advocacies while focusing on the following to fight crime and corruption:
<P>
<OL>
<LI TYPE=\"A\">VACC  Legislative Agenda
<OL>
<LI>Crime Victims’ Law to contain
<OL>
	<LI>Compensation Act and Program for Victims of Heinous Crimes
	<LI>Victims-Witness Assistance Provisions
	<LI>Anti-Recidivist Offenders provisions
</OL>
<LI>Setting up of a  Crime Victims-Witness Office or Center under the DOJ     to  provide  for  various services to victims in the course of achieving justice     and to provide for faster  and more complete victim recovery from the effects of      crime through  victim and witness assistance 
<LI>Declaration of a National Crime Victims’ Rights Week – with a corresponding Public Awareness Campaign on Crime and Justice System
<LI>Community Justice System (Barangay-based Jury System)to provide for effective community-based intervention and supervision that are critical to reduce the risk of further victimization.
<LI>Revision of the Police Orientation & Training Curriculum
<LI>Inclusion of the Crime Victims Rights and Vigilance on the Justice System as a social policy
<LI>Participatory Review of Parole/Pardon  System (with citizens’ groups)
<LI>Community-based Public Accountability Act (for all public officials in the LGUs, PNP, AFP, courts, jails, various local departments) which will require monthly reporting and accounting to the community about their actions and programs including funds and resources use. More severe penalties for public servants and doing away with the SPECIAL TREATMENT or VIP Treatment practice for erring public officials
<LI>Establishment of Community-based Multisectoral Consultation Board on the barangay level up to the provincial level to be composed of LGU, 5 pillars of justice including legitimate people’s organizations (civil society) for consultation and action-driven programs; this will be one of the mechanisms for the Community-based Public Accountability Act
<LI>Law Against Transnational Crimes like Money Laundering and NArcopolitical involvement (Money Laundering is using crime money like drug money to set up businesses to \\\"legalize\\\" the money and NArcopolitics is political groups and politicians being funded by drug syndicates and drug money)
</OL>
<LI TYPE=\"A\">Projects and Programs

<OL>
<LI>A Handbook for Crime Victims in the Philippine Setting   which can be
            distributed  directly to victims of crime with additional  pamphlet on  \\\"The 
            Criminal Justice System and You\\\"

<LI>A GUIDE TO SURVIVAL  for Family and Friends of Homicide Victims to provide assistance, information, tips
<LI>Launching a Web-based database of information  on Crime Victims’ Cases
<LI>Education curriculum development to include special curriculum on The Different Aspects of Criminal Justice and Social Policy
<LI>Launching of petitions like Parole Block Petitions on  efforts in stopping the early release of convicted murderers, death penalty for recidivist and 
      hardened heinous crimes convicts and against crime & corruption 
      fostering policies, laws and programs etc
<LI>Endorsements of programs, candidates, policies, projects that promote VACC mission to restore and maintain balance in  criminal justice system – which has put criminals\\\' rights ahead of victims\\\' rights.
<LI>Education  and political action to enhance victims’ rights, public safety, promote effective  crime-prevention measures and strengthen the rights of crime victims;   promote education prevention programs 
<LI>Organization of barangay-based VACC partnerships and alliances with five pillars of the criminal justice system with stress on alternative value education or conscientization to fight crime and corruption.
</OL>
</OL>
<P>
We may never have a crime and victim-free society in the immediate future but  we will never know if we don\'t try.  All that is required for evil to prevail is for good men to do nothing.  VACC will support in Congress all legislative acts that will address the root problems of crime – poverty of the many because of the greed of the few,
<P>
As to having different anticrime and crimevictims groups, it is the same with labor, women, peasants, national minorities and others which have different groups or organizations too.  
<P>
VACC is different from other anticrime groups because it has elevated its struggle to the level of political, economic and social concerns NOT only crime and victims\' concerns.  
<P>
VACC believes that we should not only fight crime and if we are crime victims, our concern is not only to follow up our cases until their just conclusion.  Our long term  concern must be that because we have been victimized, we must bring victimization forward as a social issue and make this a political concern in government that must be addressed at ITS ROOTS.', '', '', 'vacc@pacific.net.ph', '', '', '', '20010511114152', '', '', '2001');
