INSERT INTO senators VALUES ( '19', 'Roco', 'Raul', 'S', '302', '1995-06-30', 'N', 'Y', '0000-00-00', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<P>
Sen. Raul S. Roco is the son of a farmer and a public school teacher from Bicol. He finished elementary at 10 and high school at 14 in Ateneo de Naga.  He graduated AB English, Magna Cum Laude, at 18, and earned his law degree as Abbot\'s Awardee for Over-all Excellence at San Beda College.  He took his Master of Comparative Law as a University Fellow at the University of Pennsylvania.
<P>
Raul was the youngest president of the National Union of Students of the Philippines (NUSP), the youngest Bicolano delegate to the Constitutional Convention and the youngest president of the Integrated Bar of the Philippines.  As legal staff of Sen. Ninoy Aquino, he drafted the Study Now Pay Later Law.
<P>
He wrote the lyrics of the San Beda College Alma Mater Song.  He was executive producer of Lino Brocka’s award-winning Tinimbang Ka Ngunit Kulang.  He wrote the song Kaunting Dasal inspired by his deep-seated beliefs in hard work, study and prayer.
<P>
Representing the 2nd District of Camarines Sur, he was adjudged by the Ford Foundation and the UP Institute of Strategic and Development Studies (ISDS), First in over-all performance among legislators at the Eighth Congress for the period 1987 – 1992.  Raul was cited Outstanding by the Free Press in 1992 and 1999 and by various other publications and award bodies. 
<P>
Often alluded to as “Honorary Woman”, he authored the Women in Nation Building Law (RA 7192), the Nursing Act (RA 7164), the Anti-Sexual Sexual Harassment Law (RA 7877), the Anti-Rape Law (RA 8353), and the Child and Family Courts Act (RA 8369). 
<P>
Raul is considered the Father of the Bangko Sentral as author/sponsor of the New Central Bank Law (RA 7653).  He liberalized the banking industry (RA 7721) and strengthened the Thrift Banks (RA 7906).  He authored the Intellectual Property Code (RA 8293) and the Securities Regulation Code (RA 8792).  
<P>
Raul authored the amendment to which avoided the double taxation on overseas Filipinos (RA 8424).  He authored the bill allowing overseas Filipinos to vote (S. No. 1746).  He is author and sponsor of the bill lifting the political ad-ban (S. No. 1742).
<P>
He was member of the Board of Trustees of the University of the Philippines and other state universities.  At present, he sits in the Board of Trustees of Ateneo de Naga University.
<P>
Raul is chairman of the Committee on Banksand the Committee on Electoral Reforms.  He was recently elected to the Executive Committee of the Interparliamentary Union (IPU), the first Filipino to hold that position.
<P>
Raul is the president of Aksyon Demokratiko party. He is married to Sonia Cubillo Malasarte of Bohol, the Most Outstanding Student of the Philippines in 1964.  They have seven children, Robbie Pierre, Raul Jr., Sophia, Sareena, Rex, Synara and Nicolai.
